        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 9 at 7:27PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 727 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a shower over Fort Lupton,
or 21 miles south of Greeley, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Northeastern Thornton, eastern Longmont, northeastern Broomfield,
Brighton, Erie, Firestone, Frederick, Fort Lupton, Milliken,
Berthoud, Lochbuie, Dacono, Mead, Platteville, Hudson, Keenesburg,
Gilcrest, Milton Reservoir, Todd Creek and Wattenburg.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
